  "prompt": "How can a Nigerian citizen migrate to Canada permanently?",
  "response": "To migrate to Canada permanently, a Nigerian citizen can consider several pathways:\n\n1. Express Entry System\n- Federal Skilled Worker Program\n- Federal Skilled Trades Program\n- Canadian Experience Class\n- Requires meeting specific criteria like education, work experience, language skills\n- Points-based system\n- Need minimum language proficiency in English/French\n- Obtain Educational Credential Assessment (ECA)\n\n2. Provincial Nominee Program (PNP)\n- Different provinces have specific immigration streams\n- Requires skills matching provincial labor market needs\n- Can lead to permanent residency\n\n3. Study Permit\n- Obtain Canadian education\n- Apply for Post-Graduation Work Permit\n- Potentially transition to permanent residency\n\n4. Work Permit\n- Get job offer from Canadian employer\n- Potentially qualify for permanent residency through work experience\n\n5. Family Sponsorship\n- If you have close relatives who are Canadian citizens/permanent residents\n\n6. Start-up Visa Program\n- For entrepreneurs with innovative business ideas\n- Requires support from designated organizations\n\nKey Requirements:\n- Valid passport\n- Prove financial capability\n- Clean criminal record\n- Medical examination\n- Sufficient funds for settlement\n- Language proficiency test results\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Check official Canadian immigration website\n- Consult immigration lawyer/consultant\n- Prepare comprehensive documentation\n- Meet all eligibility criteria",
